{"_id":"O13pzLoVTTw68sBB","name":"Death's Pendulum","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Forged in the borderlands between life and the Otherworld, your zweihander deals 2d6 damage but there is a 2-in-6 chance those slain with the blade will rise in d3 rounds as vengeful undead with half HP.</p>","carryWeight":2,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"2d6","handed":"2","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/weapons/zweihander.png","effects":[]}
{"name":"Nechrubel's Whispering Script","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>A thousand skittering lines of prophecy coat your blade in a crazed patina. You may cut your hand on its edge for d2 HP damage to ask one question about something vile, blasphemous, doomed, or miserable, which the GM will answer truthfully. Each time you do this, Nechrubel takes greater interest; putting questions of his own to you, and eventually, commands.</p>","carryWeight":2,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"1d10","handed":"2","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/weapons/zweihander.png","effects":[],"_id":"VLYwtTPrdvtOt4K5"}
{"name":"Graven-Tosk Slab","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Your blade is immensely heavy, its dire blows falling like a sarcophagus lid. When you roll 8+ HP damage with your zweihander, your enemy is dazed: they lose their next action, and tests to attack them have DR -2. You stagger as well, and test defense at +2 DR for a round.</p>","carryWeight":2,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"1d10","handed":"2","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/weapons/zweihander.png","effects":[],"_id":"brpWkwsyCJXtUrID"}
{"name":"Essence Leech","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Your sword&rsquo;s hunger for anima has become your own. When your blade lands a killing blow, you may immediately reroll your Omens. On an even result, you can&rsquo;t regain Omens by resting until you sleep in a graveyard.</p>","carryWeight":2,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"1d10","handed":"2","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/weapons/zweihander.png","effects":[],"_id":"i9h1KR05zH0vODBh"}
{"name":"Damned Blade-Thrall","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"class","data":{"abilities":"<p>A CLASS FOR MÃ–RK BORG by Nathan Harrison.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Your weathered body draws sustenance from steel, 3d6+2 for Toughness. You suffer a fettered soul, 3d6-<strong>2 for Presence. </strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>You start with a zweihander and roll d4 on the armor table. Your zweihander is cursed, forever bound to you while you live.</strong> You cannot be rid of it willingly, and it weighs on you so heavily it counts as two items for carrying capacity. If you do become separated, you cannot heal by resting and take d3 damage each dawn you remain apart. On a fumbled attack, roll for an Arcane Catastrophe instead of breaking or losing your weapon. (Reroll results mentioning Powers or scrolls.)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You also begin with one of these qualities:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Weal and woe (d6)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>DEATH'S PENDULUM</li>\n<li>GRAVEN-TOSK SLAB</li>\n<li>KINDRED OF THE CHARNEL PITS</li>\n<li>ESSENCE LEECH</li>\n<li>Nechrubel&rsquo;s whispering script</li>\n<li>ANTIMATTER SOUL</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>HOW YOU CAME TO BEAR THIS BURDEN (D6)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Pried from the grip of a cemetery monument.</li>\n<li>Bought for a pittance from a merchant whose face you now cannot picture.</li>\n<li>It betrayed its former master, who found themselves fallen upon it when you pulled apart after a scuffle.</li>\n<li>Freed from ice in a Kerg&uuml;s cave guarded by a pale &amp; withered childlike creature.</li>\n<li>Left to you in the will of a reclusive Galgenbeck priest. 6&mdash;A bristly-haired demon ape rose from a stinking mud pit and offered the blade up to your hand.</li>\n<li>A bristly-haired demon ape rose from a stinking mud pit and offered the blade up to your hand.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","armorTableDie":"1d4","description":"Taking it up was a folly you did not comprehend. Your bones ache and your body is bent after so long shouldering this loathsome sword. Despite your many attempts to smash or sunder it, the only thing left broken is your spirit. Will even death free you from its bitter weight? No answer could bring comfort. So still you heft the blade, or when too weary of its heavy fate, drag it yet unscathed across the cobbles and hard earth.","omenDie":"1d4","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d10","startingItems":"morkborg-3p.class-damned-blade-thrall,Your zweihander is cursed","startingPresence":"3d6-2","startingRolls":"morkborg-3p.rolls-damned-blade-thrall,Weal and woe,1\nmorkborg-3p.rolls-damned-blade-thrall,How You Came to Bear This Burden,1","startingSilver":"2d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6","startingToughness":"3d6+2","weaponTableDie":""},"flags":{},"img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/blade-thrall.png","effects":[],"_id":"jpmK3KOXx4i3WLAA"}
{"name":"Kindred of the Charnel Pits","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>A flock of d4+1 carrion birds (d4+1 HP, claw/bite d4) is bound to you, and you to them. You can speak their squawking, screeching tongue. When the flock feeds on the fallen, you count it as a meal; if it was slain by your blade, you heal d6 HP. Your body otherwise rejects all food and drink, and you cannot benefit from either.</p>","carryWeight":2,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"1d10","handed":"2","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/weapons/zweihander.png","effects":[],"_id":"lzO0AKiy8qCeVVab"}
{"name":"Your zweihander is cursed","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"feat","data":{"description":"<ul>\n<li>Your zweihander is cursed, forever bound to you while you live.</li>\n<li>You cannot be rid of it willingly, and it weighs on you so heavily it counts as two items for carrying capacity.</li>\n<li>If you do become separated, you cannot heal by resting and take d3 damage each dawn you remain apart.</li>\n<li>On a fumbled attack, roll for an Arcane Catastrophe instead of breaking or losing your weapon. (Reroll results mentioning Powers or scrolls.)</li>\n</ul>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"flags":{},"img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/blade-thrall.png","effects":[],"_id":"sbZdkMckZxwHjITK"}
{"name":"Antimatter Soul","permission":{"default":0,"xVCY8TaEyq1Er5RJ":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"containerSpace":1,"description":"<p>Death awaits your defective, cancerous soul with abject dread, and will break the earth&rsquo;s bones to disclaim it. You are not broken until you reach negative HP, and do not die until your negative HP exceeds half your HP maximum. Whenever you become broken, the GM rolls for Misery. If you die, a Misery is immediately fulfilled.</p>","carryWeight":2,"equipped":false,"price":0,"quantity":1,"damageDie":"1d10","handed":"2","weaponType":"melee"},"flags":{},"img":"systems/morkborg/icons/items/weapons/zweihander.png","effects":[],"_id":"ulMMAdcpZLCfMW73"}
